37 5. No port authority shall be required to pay any
38 taxes or any assessments whatsoever to this state or to any
39 political subdivisions, municipality, or other governmental
40 agency of this state. The notes and bonds of every port
41 authority and the income therefrom shall, at all times, be
42 exempt from any taxes and any assessments, except for death
43 and gift taxes and taxes on transfers. Additionally, the
44 leases of both real and personal property by or to any port
45 authority involving the issuance of bonds authorized under
46 this chapter shall be exempt from taxation. A port
47 authority issuing bonds under this chapter for incentivized
48 development shall require the developer of any project which
